From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: VyOS LS1046A CI <ci@vyos-ls1046a>
Date: Thu, 29 May 2026 06:10:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] dpaa1: M3-3 step 7 sub-increment 3 - true-ZC RX Recover
 read-side (xsk_zc_rx_recovered counter, dormant recovery branch)

M3-3 step 7 (true zero-copy RX, spec sec 6.1.7) has a three-mechanism
plan: (1) Recognise XSK-pool-sourced FDs by matching fd->bpid against
priv->xsk_bpid[band]; (2) Recover the xdp_buff from the XSK chunk via the
xsk_buff path instead of the kernel-page build_skb() path; (3) reProgram
the FMan RX port's primary BPID to the XSK pool's BPID so FMan DMAs
directly into XSK chunks (the hardware-risky MURAM write).

The de-risking cadence so far:
  - 0083  observational xsk_rx_branch (FD reached the bound qband)
  - 0093  sub-increment 1: xsk_zc_eligible (mechanism-1 Recognise
          arithmetic in the RX hot path) -- 17th xsk_* counter
  - 0094  sub-increment 2: xsk_zc_rx_armed (mechanism-3 reprogram READ
          side at attach time, no FMan write) -- 18th xsk_* counter
  - 0095  sub-increment 3 GATE: xsk_fill_guard_block (FILL-ring
          double-release guard, crash-defense) -- 19th xsk_* counter

This patch lands the READ side of mechanism 2 (Recover): the recovery
branch in rx_default_dqrr(), wired but DORMANT. It is the mirror of how
0094 landed mechanism-3's read side before its write: the recovery code
path is compiled, reachable, and arithmetically proven, but it can NEVER
fire on the shipping datapath because mechanism 3 (the FMan RX port BPID
reprogram, spec sec 6.1.7 line "Program") has NOT run. While FMan
continues to DMA into the kernel page pool (priv->dpaa_bp->bpid), every
live FD carries the kernel page BPID, so fd->bpid == priv->xsk_bpid[band]
is false and the recovery branch is dead code -- exactly as on the
default/vpp shipping path today.

Why land a dormant Recover branch now, before the reprogram write:

  - It closes the last *read-only* gap in the three-mechanism plan.
    After this, all three mechanisms have their observable half landed
    (Recognise=0093, reProgram-read=0094, Recover-read=0096) and only
    the single hardware-risky reProgram WRITE (the MURAM BPID swap) plus
    the productive xsk_buff_recv()/xdp_do_redirect() body remain -- to be
    authored as the final sub-increment 4 ONLY after the 0093/0094/0095
    gate counters are DUT-validated under load (spec sec 6.1.12 entry
    preconditions: xsk_zc_rx_armed > 0 AND xsk_fill_guard_block == 0).

  - It makes the Recover *decision point* observable from userspace
    (ethtool -S | grep xsk_zc_rx_recovered) so that, the instant the
    sub-increment-4 reprogram lands and FMan starts DMAing into XSK
    chunks, this counter begins to climb in lock-step with xsk_zc_eligible
    -- proving the Recover branch is taken for exactly the FDs the
    Recognise test flags, with zero datapath risk added by THIS patch.

What 0096 does (three additive, datapath-neutral edits):

  - dpaa_eth.c: inside the existing 0083/0093 RCU read-section in
    rx_default_dqrr(), within the `if (_xp)` arm, AFTER the 0093
    `if (fd->bpid == priv->xsk_bpid[_band]) priv->xsk_zc_eligible++;`
    recognition test, add a guarded Recover decision: when the FD is
    XSK-pool-sourced (same bpid match) AND the band is armed for true-ZC
    (priv->xsk_zc_rx_armed) AND the FILL-ring guard has never fired
    (!priv->xsk_fill_guard_block), bump priv->xsk_zc_rx_recovered. The FD
    then continues through the UNCHANGED mainline skbuf path -- no
    xsk_buff_recv(), no xdp_do_redirect(), no datapath divergence. The
    productive recovery body (recover the xdp_buff from the XSK chunk and
    redirect into the XSKMAP instead of build_skb()) is the deferred
    sub-increment-4 work, gated behind the DUT validation of 0093/0094/
    0095 and the FMan-port reprogram WRITE.

  - dpaa_eth.h: u64 xsk_zc_rx_recovered; appended to the contiguous xsk_*
    counter block (after xsk_fill_guard_block from 0095). 20th xsk_*
    counter.

  - dpaa_ethtool.c: "xsk_zc_rx_recovered" appended to dpaa_stats_xsk[]
    (the value-emit loop is length-driven; no loop edit needed).

Why this is byte-identical to mainline / 0095 on default/vpp: on the
default flavor no XSK pool is ever bound, so priv->xsk_bpid stays 0 while
a live FD always carries a non-zero kernel page BPID -- the bpid-match
test is false and the Recover branch is dead code. Even on a future vpp
flavor that binds XDP_ZEROCOPY, until sub-increment 4 reprograms the FMan
RX port BPID the FMan keeps DMAing into the kernel page pool, so fd->bpid
remains the kernel BPID, the branch still never fires, and copy-mode RX
(patch 0089) is preserved bit-for-bit. The added cost on the hot path is
a single integer compare already dominated by the 0093 test it extends.

Spec sec 6.1.7 true-ZC mechanism 2 (Recover, read side) + sec 6.1.13.

Signed-off-by: VyOS LS1046A CI <ci@vyos-ls1046a>
---
--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/dpaa_eth.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/dpaa_eth.c
@@ -2851,20 +2851,42 @@
 
 rcu_read_lock();
 _xp = rcu_dereference(priv->xsk_pool[_band]);
 if (_xp) {
 priv->xsk_rx_branch++;
 /* M3-3 step 7 sub-increment 1 (patch 0093): the FD
  * reached a qband with a bound XSK pool. If FMan also
  * DMA'd it into an XSK-pool BMan chunk, fd->bpid equals
  * the dedicated BPID recorded by xsk_pool_attach().
  * Until sub-increment 2 reprograms the FMan RX port's
  * primary BPID, fd->bpid stays the kernel page BPID and
  * this stays 0 -- proving the recognition path is sound
  * with zero datapath risk. Spec sec 6.1.7 / 6.1.10.
  */
-if (fd->bpid == priv->xsk_bpid[_band])
-priv->xsk_zc_eligible++;
+if (fd->bpid == priv->xsk_bpid[_band]) {
+priv->xsk_zc_eligible++;
+/* M3-3 step 7 sub-increment 3 (patch 0096): true-ZC RX
+ * Recover read-side. The FD was DMA'd by FMan into an
+ * XSK-pool BMan chunk (recognised just above) AND the band
+ * was armed for true-ZC at attach (xsk_zc_rx_armed, 0094)
+ * AND the FILL-ring double-release guard has never fired
+ * (xsk_fill_guard_block == 0, 0095). Under those conditions
+ * sub-increment 4 will Recover the xdp_buff from the XSK
+ * chunk and xdp_do_redirect() it into the XSKMAP instead of
+ * the kernel build_skb() path. Here we only OBSERVE that the
+ * Recover decision would be taken -- the FD still travels
+ * the unchanged mainline skbuf path below, so there is NO
+ * datapath change. This counter stays 0 until sub-increment
+ * 4 reprograms the FMan RX port BPID (the hardware-risky
+ * MURAM write, gated on DUT validation of 0094/0095 per
+ * spec sec 6.1.12); once it does, this climbs in lock-step
+ * with xsk_zc_eligible, proving Recover fires for exactly
+ * the recognised FDs. Spec sec 6.1.7 / 6.1.13.
+ */
+if (priv->xsk_zc_rx_armed &&
+    !priv->xsk_fill_guard_block)
+priv->xsk_zc_rx_recovered++;
+}
 }
 rcu_read_unlock();
 }
 
--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/dpaa_eth.h
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/dpaa_eth.h
@@ -338,6 +338,25 @@
  */
 u64 xsk_fill_guard_block;
 
+/* M3-3 step 7 sub-increment 3 (patch 0096): true-ZC RX Recover
+ * read-side. Bumped in rx_default_dqrr() when an FD is
+ * recognised as XSK-pool-sourced (fd->bpid == xsk_bpid[band],
+ * the 0093 test) AND the band is armed for true-ZC
+ * (xsk_zc_rx_armed, 0094) AND the FILL-ring guard has never
+ * fired (xsk_fill_guard_block == 0, 0095) -- i.e. the Recover
+ * decision would be taken. Strictly diagnostic: the FD still
+ * travels the unchanged mainline skbuf path, so the RX datapath
+ * is byte-identical to mainline. Stays 0 until sub-increment 4
+ * reprograms the FMan RX port's primary BPID (the hardware-risky
+ * MURAM write); once FMan DMAs into XSK chunks this climbs in
+ * lock-step with xsk_zc_eligible, proving the Recover branch is
+ * taken for exactly the recognised FDs before the productive
+ * xsk_buff_recv()/xdp_do_redirect() body is wired. Unreached on
+ * default/vpp (no XDP_ZEROCOPY bind / no reprogram).
+ * Spec sec 6.1.7 true-ZC mechanism 2 (Recover) + sec 6.1.13.
+ */
+u64 xsk_zc_rx_recovered;
+
 /* M3-3b (patch 0086): FMan PCD capability bitmask snapshot taken
  * at probe via dpaa_fman_get_caps(). 0 on mainline ucode 106 ->
  * all fman_cc_tree_/fman_hm_/fman_pol_ helpers short-circuit
--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/dpaa_ethtool.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/dpaa_ethtool.c
@@ -73,6 +73,7 @@
 "xsk_zc_eligible",
 "xsk_zc_rx_armed",
 "xsk_fill_guard_block",
+"xsk_zc_rx_recovered",
 };
 
 /* HW-offload (PCD-cap) counters (M3-3b / patch 0086). Order MUST match
